838	+//! `SYS_FORK` — clone a blocked parent into a free process slot.
839	+//!
840	+//! PM owns the process tree; the kernel's half of fork is mechanical
841	+//! (MINIX 3 `kernel/system/do_fork.c`): validate, copy the parent's saved
842	+//! state into the child slot PM picked, give the child its own address space
843	+//! (an eager page-by-page copy — CoW is deferred), and hand back the child's
844	+//! endpoint. PM then drives `VM_FORK`, `SCHEDULING_START`, and the
845	+//! `SYS_PRIVCTL(PRIVCTL_SET_USER)` release before replying to both halves.
846	+//!
847	+//! The parent must be RECEIVE-blocked with no pending delivery ("fork is done
848	+//! synchronously", MINIX parity): in the live flow it is mid-`SENDREC` to PM,
849	+//! so its full register frame is parked in `Proc::regs` with `x0` already
850	+//! holding the SENDREC's `OK`. The child copies that frame *verbatim* — both
851	+//! processes resume after the same `svc` instruction and read their own reply
852	+//! buffer; PM's reply `m_type` (child pid vs 0) is the only discriminator,
853	+//! not a patched return register.
854	+//!
855	+//! The child is created **frozen**: `RTS_RECEIVING` (a faithful mid-SENDREC
856	+//! receiver, so PM's reply delivers normally) plus `RTS_NO_PRIV` (the
857	+//! stub-E freeze gate — `SYS_PRIVCTL` releases it once VM and SCHED know
858	+//! about the child). It is not enqueued; `rts_unset` admits it when the last
859	+//! block bit clears. `priv_id` is inherited from the parent — the shared
860	+//! `USER_PRIV_ID` slot (MINIX's `static_priv` model), which is what lets PM's
861	+//! reply pass `mini_send`'s `ipc_to` check before the release.
862	+//!
863	+//! The child consumes the slot's **stored** endpoint rather than minting one:
864	+//! `SYS_EXIT` bumped the generation when it freed the slot, so a recycled
865	+//! slot's new occupant is unreachable through any stale endpoint.
866	+//!
867	+//! Target-taking (routed beside `SYS_EXIT` in `kernel_call_dispatch`); trust
868	+//! model identical to `do_vmctl` — the `k_call_mask` gate is the only check,
869	+//! and PM is the intended sole holder.
